08/12/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The US and German governments will provide financial and technical assistance for Croatian projects, local media reported on Tuesday (7 December). The US Congress adopted a bill under which Croatia will be granted $20m in aid as part of the Support to Eastern European Democracies programme. The United States will also allocate $0.7m to prevent the spread of weapons of mass destruction. Germany, meanwhile, will allocate 1.8m euros, in part for a project promoting economic growth and employment. (HINA, HRT, AFP - 07/12/04) 
